Feedback:
The internal indicator lamp ("Internal Indicator Lamp") is lit, and no observable internal fault is detected with the lamp itself. This confirms that power is being correctly supplied to the branch and that the circuit up to the lamp functions nominally. Since this lamp is connected in parallel with the main load, the main load is expected to operate under the same voltage conditions. Therefore, if the main load is not operating or experiencing issues, the likely causes are:

  - BurnedFilaments (faulty main load filament/open circuit within the main load)
  - LampImproperlyInstalled (main load not seated/installed correctly)

